The paper proposes a deep learning-based method for traffic flow prediction, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also deals with traffic congestion, which is a problem related to smart cities and intelligent transportation systems, indicating the possibility of the paper belonging to the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses traffic data obtained from traffic control stations, which suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
